@BannedGecko $C was fun to trade back in the 90&#39;s...Iacocca (not Dimon).  Had the toll free number for Kennedy Cabot or Schwab 1, 
or could use the Quotron at the Schwab office.  Had to factor in round trip commissions before you&#39;d even start to make any money.   
$AAPL...well, the sell in Jan. 94 did turn a profit.

@Roll_Dem_Bones so back in the day. I’m going to the 90s.  Folks like you would be better suited for swing trading. Not a session trade. 

And honestly, swing trading is much easier, higher probability, and lower risk compared to day traders who have to remove risk at the end of every session. 

Look at charts on the daily with a 30 day span. Find stocks that are easy to hide in between the big traders. Like an $AAPL .  You can easily identify patterns and the betas. Set limits and stops.
